This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of term statistics in real-time search. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it focuses on Twitter, a social network. Additionally, it could be classified under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it discusses the design of search systems. The paper also involves data analysis, which could place it under the Statistical Learning (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, it could be classified under the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with term frequency and document frequency.
